abstract: PERRY'S victory on Lake Erie is a glorious event in our country's history, and deserving a glorious commemoration. The States of the Northwest, and the Lake Cities in particular, regard its anniversary as peculiarly interesting to themselves. Its celebration has not been regularly kept up, but the enthusiasm which characterizes its commemoration when the people do get in the humor for it, amply atones for the irregularity of its occurrence.

abstract: THE NEW "BRICK CHURCH." --Dr. SPRING'S church, at the corner of Fifth-avenue and Thirty-seventh-street, is so nearly compledted as probably to be ready for occupancy by the 1st of November.
